AU  - Guha, Ashok
JO  - Journal of Development Economics
VL  - 31
IS  - 1
SP  - 1
EP  - 12
PY  - 1989
DA  - 1989/07/01/
SN  - 0304-3878
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3878(89)90028-X
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030438788990028X
AB  - If (1) there is a long-term relationship between consumption and labour efficiency, (2) long employment contracts are possible and (3) production is seasonal, a trade-off emerges between positive effects of permanent contracts on productivity and the costly seasonal idleness of permanent labour. Possible outcomes include (1) co-existence of casual and permanent contracts with number of workers affecting proportion of permanent to temporary employees but not output – classical disguised unemployment, (2) exclusively casual employment with output negatively related to workforce – Leibenstein-Mazumdar surplus labour, and (3) permanent contracts only with open unemployment and a positive relationship between number employed and output – the Mirrlees-Bliss-Stern-Stiglitz solution. Conditions are derived for each solution.
ER  - 

